The paper deals with improving the visual quality of lossy image compression using deep learning CNNs. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves training a model to identify semantic regions in an image, which could also fall under the sub-categories of Multimedia (cs.MM) and Information Retrieval (cs.IR). The use of deep learning techniques also suggests that the paper could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves designing a CNN architecture specifically for image compression, which could also fall under the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
